<outline text="OPML"/>
<outline text="outline">
<outline text="An outline is a collection of nodes that are organized in two dimensions: serial and hierarchic. The topmost level of an outline's hierarchic organization is called level 0. Nodes that are hierarchically subjunctive to a given node are called subnodes , or descendants, of that node. Subnodes one level down from a given node are called child nodes, and the given node is their parent. Nodes that share a parent node are called sibling nodes. The topmost set of sibling nodes is said to be at level 0 of the outline. Nodes contain arbitrary sorts of information, some of which is commonly displayed to the user. "/>
</outline>
</outline>
